The render-time “skinning mode” is not a choice between different primitive classes in this path: `SkeletalAppearance2` expects every display LOD primitive to be `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` and then sets `SM_noSkinning`, `SM_hardSkinning`, or `SM_softSkinning` on it before submitting. I’m checking mesh construction now to confirm where those primitives are made and whether any hardware-skin alternative exists in these directories.
